docs/components/alert#emphasis-variants","content":"All 7 emphasis categories. Each variant carries a distinct visual accent and semantic icon so the type of message is never communicated by color alone."},"39":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-15","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#dismissible","content":"When an `onClose` callback is provided, a dismiss button is rendered. The component does not manage its own visibility — the parent is responsible for unmounting or hiding the alert when `onClose` fires."},"40":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-16","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#with-action","content":"Pass a `Button` to the `actions` slot to give the user a clear path to resolve the alert."},"41":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-17","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#keyboard","content":"Key"},"42":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-18","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#keyboard","content":"Description"},"43":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-19","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#keyboard","content":"`Tab`"},"44":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-20","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#keyboard","content":"Moves focus to the dismiss button or action button"},"45":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-21","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#keyboard","content":"`Space` / `Enter`"},"46":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-22","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#keyboard","content":"Activates the focused button"},"47":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-23","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#screen-readers","content":"The alert container uses `role=\"alert\"`, which creates an ARIA live region. When an alert is rendered or its content changes, screen readers announce the message automatically — the user does not need to navigate to the alert to hear it."},"48":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-24","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#dismiss-button-label","content":"The dismiss button defaults to `aria-label=\"Close\"`. Override it via `ariaLabels={{ close: '...' }}` to provide more specific context for screen readers (e.g. `\"Dismiss payment warning\"`). This is especially useful when multiple alerts are visible at the same time."},"49":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-25","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#best-practices","content":"Write alert content from the user's perspective: describe what happened and what they can do next, not the underlying technical error."},"50":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-26","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#best-practices","content":"Use `critical` only when the user truly cannot continue without resolving the issue. Overusing it reduces its impact."},"51":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-27","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#best-practices","content":"Always provide a `title` when the alert includes a dismiss button — it improves the reading experience for screen reader users."},"52":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-28","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#best-practices","content":"When using `actions`, prefer `secondary` or `tertiary` Button variants. Avoid placing a primary action inside an alert."},"53":{"id":"/docs/components/alert-29","page_id":"/docs/components/alert","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/alert#best-practices","content":"Do not stack multiple alerts of the same emphasis; c