s you to change the HTML tag of the `Text` component."},"755":{"id":"/docs/components/text-11","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#align","content":"Setting the `align` prop allows you to change the alignment of the text. You can choose from `start`, `center`, `end`, or `justify`.\n`start` works like `left` and `end` works like `right`. These keywords support RTL languages so you do not need to worry about the language of the text."},"756":{"id":"/docs/components/text-12","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#max-lines","content":"Setting the `maxLines` prop allows you to limit the number of lines of text that are displayed using an ellipsis. In browsers that don't support multiline text truncation using `line-clamp`, the text will be truncated after a single line regardless of the number provided for `maxLines`."},"757":{"id":"/docs/components/text-13","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"Setting the `wrap` prop allows you to change the wrapping of the text. The values can be `wrap`, `nowrap`, `balance`, `pretty`, or `stable`."},"758":{"id":"/docs/components/text-14","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`wrap` is the setting that is most commonly used. For most elements you will not to explicitly set this."},"759":{"id":"/docs/components/text-15","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`nowrap` should be avoided except in cases where it is important to prevent the text from wrapping."},"760":{"id":"/docs/components/text-16","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`balance` is most commonly used for headlines, titles, and labels."},"761":{"id":"/docs/components/text-17","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`pretty` is most commonly used for body text."},"762":{"id":"/docs/components/text-18","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`stable` is commonly used for editable text, such as textareas."},"763":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"page","content":"TextField","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field"},"764":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-0","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field","content":"TextField is a single-line or multiline text input with optional label, description, and error message. Use it in forms for short answers (email, search, name) or longer content (comments). It supports optional leading and trailing text adornments (e.g. currency or units)."},"765":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-1","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"Features"},"766":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-2","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#installation","content":"Installation"},"767":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-3","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#props","content":"Props"},"768":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-4","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#examples","content":"Examples"},"769":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-5","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#basic","content":"Basic"},"770":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-6","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#controlled","con